1
00:00:41,160 --> 00:00:43,000
I never expected the world's greatest detective

2
00:00:43,360 --> 00:00:44,720
to believe that lighting lamps drives away ghosts.

3
00:00:45,640 --> 00:00:46,760
Because I really saw it.

4
00:00:47,880 --> 00:00:48,400
Saw what?

5
00:00:49,400 --> 00:00:50,440
I saw the ghost within my heart.

6
00:00:56,000 --> 00:00:58,280
Back then, I was just a Magistrate.

7
00:00:59,320 --> 00:01:00,280
I misjudged a case,

8
00:01:01,080 --> 00:01:02,280
which led to the death of a woman.

9
00:01:04,000 --> 00:01:05,560
This is my greatest fear.

10
00:01:06,040 --> 00:01:08,160
So I suspect there is something strange in this forest

11
00:01:08,360 --> 00:01:09,680
that can evoke the fear in people's hearts.

12
00:01:10,600 --> 00:01:11,480
Did you not see anything?

13
00:01:13,200 --> 00:01:13,520
Never.

14
00:01:14,120 --> 00:01:15,800
I just felt a bit dizzy.

15
00:01:18,160 --> 00:01:19,960
Then our Vice Minister truly has a clear conscience.

16
00:01:22,600 --> 00:01:23,120
Guiyi.

17
00:01:23,920 --> 00:01:24,440
You see?

18
00:01:25,280 --> 00:01:27,800
This is the master you idolize.

19
00:01:28,840 --> 00:01:29,440
So what?

20
00:01:45,120 --> 00:01:45,720
Marong Flower.

21
00:01:49,560 --> 00:01:50,360
What is a Marong Flower?

22
00:01:52,120 --> 00:01:52,600
It is a type of

23
00:01:53,480 --> 00:01:54,920
extremely rare herb from the Western Regions.

24
00:01:55,720 --> 00:01:56,240
Colorless and odorless,

25
00:01:56,800 --> 00:01:57,720
with strong hallucinogenic properties.

26
00:01:58,200 --> 00:01:58,720
Its pollen

27
00:01:59,600 --> 00:02:00,280
can travel for miles.

28
00:02:08,000 --> 00:02:08,240
Lao Yao.

29
00:02:08,920 --> 00:02:09,120
Mm.

30
00:02:09,560 --> 00:02:10,520
If I act strangely later,

31
00:02:11,120 --> 00:02:11,560
light the lamp immediately.

32
00:02:13,800 --> 00:02:14,040
Okay.

33
00:02:26,280 --> 00:02:27,400
Shentu Baiqi.

34
00:02:40,440 --> 00:02:41,920
You misjudged a case.

35
00:02:42,360 --> 00:02:43,320
You are unworthy of being a Magistrate.

36
00:02:44,560 --> 00:02:45,280
I caught the murderer.

37
00:02:46,720 --> 00:02:47,760
I have already cleared your name.

38
00:02:48,440 --> 00:02:49,800
But I am already dead.

39
00:02:51,440 --> 00:02:52,240
I am atoning for it.

40
00:02:53,000 --> 00:02:54,240
I have investigated cases desperately all these years,

41
00:02:54,720 --> 00:02:56,360
just so there would be no more injustice in the world.

42
00:02:57,640 --> 00:02:58,200
I am atoning for it.

43
00:02:59,320 --> 00:03:00,120
I am already atoning for it.

44
00:03:13,040 --> 00:03:13,320
Shentu.

45
00:03:14,680 --> 00:03:14,920
Shentu.

46
00:03:21,560 --> 00:03:21,840
How is it?

47
00:03:23,320 --> 00:03:23,800
I understand now.

48
00:03:25,000 --> 00:03:26,320
Just now at Old Man Yu's house,

49
00:03:27,160 --> 00:03:27,760
inside the lamp oil,

50
00:03:28,320 --> 00:03:28,840
there was a scent.

51
00:03:30,080 --> 00:03:30,680
That scent

52
00:03:31,400 --> 00:03:32,000
is the antidote.

53
00:03:36,800 --> 00:03:39,480
Shrouding the whole township in the Marong Flower's hallucinations,

54
00:03:40,240 --> 00:03:42,080
and then using the antidote in the lamp oil to neutralize it.

55
00:03:42,760 --> 00:03:43,200
By doing this,

56
00:03:43,640 --> 00:03:45,200
they maintain the people's normal lives.

57
00:03:46,160 --> 00:03:46,840
When night falls,

58
00:03:47,560 --> 00:03:48,040
whoever they want to kill,

59
00:03:48,920 --> 00:03:50,000
they just extinguish their oil lamp.

60
00:03:50,800 --> 00:03:51,920
Perhaps this is the truth.

61
00:03:53,840 --> 00:03:55,560
But why go to such great lengths?

62
00:03:56,000 --> 00:03:57,680
Making the whole township deplete their wealth,

63
00:03:58,640 --> 00:03:59,400
burdened by these oil lamps.

64
00:04:03,760 --> 00:04:04,320
Could it be

65
00:04:05,320 --> 00:04:06,720
the entire township is his enemy?

66
00:04:08,840 --> 00:04:10,600
First, let's find the body dumping site Lady Xiaomu mentioned.

67
00:04:11,160 --> 00:04:12,200
To see if there are any new clues.

68
00:04:12,520 --> 00:04:12,760
Mm.

69
00:04:13,760 --> 00:04:14,360
It should be over there.

70
00:04:20,040 --> 00:04:20,240
Let's go.

71
00:04:52,920 --> 00:04:53,480
This road

72
00:04:53,960 --> 00:04:54,800
is a point of no return.

73
00:05:00,840 --> 00:05:01,080
Wait.

74
00:05:01,920 --> 00:05:02,200
Something's wrong.

75
00:05:18,080 --> 00:05:19,000
This is actually a cliff.

76
00:05:25,520 --> 00:05:26,640
If no one leads you out,

77
00:05:27,680 --> 00:05:29,280
you will never leave Wanling Township.

78
00:05:29,920 --> 00:05:31,200
They don't want anyone leaving Wanling Township.

79
00:05:32,080 --> 00:05:33,040
So they made fake road signs.

80
00:05:33,760 --> 00:05:34,680
Anyone who wants to leave

81
00:05:35,480 --> 00:05:36,480
will be led to the edge of the cliff.

82
00:05:36,880 --> 00:05:37,200
Not bad.

83
00:05:38,360 --> 00:05:41,080
You people from Dali Temple are indeed extraordinary.

84
00:05:42,440 --> 00:05:44,520
But you found out too late.

85
00:05:44,920 --> 00:05:45,480
You audacious scoundrels!

86
00:05:45,840 --> 00:05:46,480
You reckless fools!

87
00:05:47,120 --> 00:05:48,880
Daring to turn your weapons against Dali Temple!

88
00:05:49,200 --> 00:05:50,880
If you die at the bottom of this cliff,

89
00:05:51,160 --> 00:05:52,040
who would know?

90
00:05:52,280 --> 00:05:53,280
If someone comes to investigate,

91
00:05:53,760 --> 00:05:54,520
just like you,

92
00:05:54,960 --> 00:05:56,480
no one will leave Wanling Township.

93
00:05:59,080 --> 00:05:59,480
Get them!

94
00:06:21,040 --> 00:06:22,280
Let's see what they fear in their hearts.

95
00:06:22,480 --> 00:06:22,680
Mm.

96
00:06:37,000 --> 00:06:37,200
It's her.

97
00:06:37,520 --> 00:06:38,560
It is... it's her, it's her!

98
00:06:40,240 --> 00:06:40,840
Don't come for me!

99
00:06:41,600 --> 00:06:42,040
Don't come for me!

100
00:06:43,160 --> 00:06:44,080
Don't come for me!

101
00:06:44,240 --> 00:06:45,280
Don't... don't come for me!

102
00:06:45,640 --> 00:06:46,400
He was the one who wanted you dead!

103
00:06:46,840 --> 00:06:47,800
It had nothing to do with me!

104
00:06:49,520 --> 00:06:50,640
Ask him. Who is he?

105
00:06:52,640 --> 00:06:52,920
Stay back!

106
00:06:53,440 --> 00:06:53,800
Stay back!

107
00:06:54,400 --> 00:06:55,520
Who is he?

108
00:06:55,640 --> 00:06:56,600
Village Head Qian Yu.

109
00:06:56,760 --> 00:06:57,200
No, no, no!

110
00:06:57,440 --> 00:06:57,640
No!

111
00:06:57,800 --> 00:06:58,120
It's not Qian Yu!

112
00:06:58,360 --> 00:06:59,640
He is... he is Wang Xing!

113
00:07:01,000 --> 00:07:02,560
Why did you harm me?

114
00:07:02,920 --> 00:07:03,600
Don't kill me!

115
00:07:05,800 --> 00:07:06,240
Don't kill me!

116
00:07:30,560 --> 00:07:31,160
Ghost!

117
00:07:35,240 --> 00:07:35,880
Please spare me!

118
00:07:36,240 --> 00:07:36,880
Please spare me!

119
00:07:37,080 --> 00:07:38,080
Please spare me!

120
00:07:39,200 --> 00:07:40,640
You planted Marong Flowers in the forest,

121
00:07:41,200 --> 00:07:41,920
used this red dress

122
00:07:43,160 --> 00:07:44,480
to trigger the fear in their hearts,

123
00:07:45,560 --> 00:07:47,080
and controlled them with the antidote in the lamp oil.

124
00:07:48,040 --> 00:07:48,920
Whoever you wanted to kill,

125
00:07:49,280 --> 00:07:50,000
you just extinguished their lamp.

126
00:07:50,640 --> 00:07:50,840
Is that right?

127
00:07:52,400 --> 00:07:52,880
Those who survived

128
00:07:53,520 --> 00:07:55,000
also lived in constant fear,

129
00:07:56,240 --> 00:07:56,920
burning lamps day and night,

130
00:07:57,560 --> 00:07:58,360
exhausting their wealth,

131
00:07:59,040 --> 00:07:59,760
until they finally starved

132
00:08:00,000 --> 00:08:00,400
or froze to death.

133
00:08:01,120 --> 00:08:01,840
Am I right?

134
00:08:02,760 --> 00:08:04,560
Why did you want to kill everyone in the township?

135
00:08:10,520 --> 00:08:14,240
It wasn't me who killed the people of Wanling Township.

136
00:08:16,960 --> 00:08:17,640
It was him.

137
00:08:19,800 --> 00:08:22,000
Back then, when this group

138
00:08:22,840 --> 00:08:24,880
of damned people were about to starve to death,

139
00:08:25,360 --> 00:08:27,280
it was the old Village Head Qian Yu who took them in.

140
00:08:27,920 --> 00:08:29,480
But these people were idle,

141
00:08:29,480 --> 00:08:30,360
lazy, and gluttonous.

142
00:08:30,960 --> 00:08:32,400
The old Village Head never complained.

143
00:08:33,160 --> 00:08:34,240
But eventually, there came a day

144
00:08:36,640 --> 00:08:38,280
when Wanling Township could no longer support them.

145
00:08:40,720 --> 00:08:41,200
Young man.

146
00:08:44,200 --> 00:08:44,720
Young man.

147
00:08:49,000 --> 00:08:49,680
Well...

148
00:08:50,800 --> 00:08:51,880
I came today

149
00:08:52,840 --> 00:08:54,960
to discuss something with you.

150
00:08:56,640 --> 00:08:57,560
What is it, Village Head Qian?

151
00:08:58,400 --> 00:09:00,000
You aren't trying to chase us away, are you?

152
00:09:00,080 --> 00:09:00,680
Uh...

153
00:09:01,480 --> 00:09:03,560
Resources in the township have been tight lately.

154
00:09:04,320 --> 00:09:05,680
We've prepared some grain for everyone

155
00:09:06,080 --> 00:09:06,840
to eat on your journey.

156
00:09:07,880 --> 00:09:08,840
You've been away for so long,

157
00:09:09,520 --> 00:09:10,920
it's time to go back home and visit.

158
00:09:13,080 --> 00:09:15,040
I heard Village Head Qian's daughter is getting married.

159
00:09:16,040 --> 00:09:18,560
At least let us have a cup of wedding wine before we go.

160
00:09:18,840 --> 00:09:19,120
Well...

161
00:09:21,880 --> 00:09:23,000
A drop of help earns gratitude,

162
00:09:24,960 --> 00:09:26,040
a bucket breeds resentment.

163
00:09:28,800 --> 00:09:30,800
Wanling Township was their benefactor!

164
00:09:32,000 --> 00:09:33,600
An entire township of people...

165
00:09:35,680 --> 00:09:37,240
It took them just one night.

166
00:09:38,720 --> 00:09:39,640
Just one night!

167
00:09:41,040 --> 00:09:42,760
Thank you all for coming to our wedding.

168
00:09:42,960 --> 00:09:43,920
Please eat and drink to your heart's content.

169
00:09:44,040 --> 00:09:44,440
Thank you.

170
00:09:44,840 --> 00:09:46,240
Neighbors, please enjoy the feast!

171
00:09:47,000 --> 00:09:48,040
Great!

172
00:09:48,840 --> 00:09:50,200
Come, let's go toast over there.

173
00:09:56,800 --> 00:09:57,480
A toast to everyone!

174
00:09:57,960 --> 00:09:59,240
Come, come, let's drink!

175
00:09:59,720 --> 00:10:00,120
Thank you for the honor.

176
00:10:00,480 --> 00:10:00,840
Thank you.

177
00:10:14,840 --> 00:10:15,960
Let's have a drink!

178
00:10:16,120 --> 00:10:16,440
Here!

179
00:10:17,560 --> 00:10:18,040
My wife.

180
00:10:24,160 --> 00:10:24,640
Are you alright?

181
00:10:37,400 --> 00:10:40,800
Luckily, that night I went to the county town to have fun

182
00:10:41,400 --> 00:10:42,200
and returned late,

183
00:10:42,200 --> 00:10:43,080
so I escaped the disaster.

184
00:10:43,760 --> 00:10:46,320
Otherwise, the tragedy of Wanling Township

185
00:10:47,000 --> 00:10:49,240
would never have been known to anyone.

186
00:10:50,320 --> 00:10:51,040
Quick, quick, quick!

187
00:10:55,120 --> 00:10:55,720
Hurry up, everyone!

188
00:11:11,280 --> 00:11:12,760
They occupied our homes

189
00:11:14,040 --> 00:11:15,240
Used our names

190
00:11:17,520 --> 00:11:19,520
If you officials have any humanity left

191
00:11:20,840 --> 00:11:21,680
Then step aside

192
00:11:23,040 --> 00:11:24,560
Let me kill this jerk

193
00:11:30,240 --> 00:11:32,040
He committed acts that enrage both gods and men

194
00:11:33,120 --> 00:11:33,920
He must die

195
00:11:35,600 --> 00:11:36,360
Tonight, I make the call

196
00:11:37,640 --> 00:11:38,680
You can choose to kill him

197
00:11:40,080 --> 00:11:42,560
And we will pretend we never came to Wanling Township

198
00:11:43,760 --> 00:11:45,280
You can also hand him over to the Dali Temple

199
00:11:45,720 --> 00:11:46,800
Let the Great Tang laws punish him

200
00:11:47,440 --> 00:11:48,200
And announce it to the world

201
00:11:52,280 --> 00:11:52,680
Sun Jia

202
00:11:54,080 --> 00:11:54,520
Trust me

203
00:11:56,000 --> 00:11:57,200
Compared to the punishment of the Great Tang laws

204
00:11:57,680 --> 00:11:58,360
If you kill him

205
00:11:59,320 --> 00:12:00,520
It is just giving him a quick release

206
00:12:02,360 --> 00:12:02,880
I promise

207
00:12:04,280 --> 00:12:06,760
His infamy will spread to every corner of the Great Tang

208
00:12:08,040 --> 00:12:09,080
Reviled by ten thousand generations

209
00:12:20,840 --> 00:12:22,040
Can I trust you?

210
00:12:24,440 --> 00:12:25,280
I keep my word

211
00:12:49,600 --> 00:12:49,880
My Lord

212
00:12:50,640 --> 00:12:51,840
This corpse has a brandy nose

213
00:12:52,400 --> 00:12:53,800
He is the Western merchant, Cyrus

214
00:12:54,880 --> 00:12:56,120
This one wearing Dashi clothing

215
00:12:56,600 --> 00:12:57,160
Is Adudan

216
00:13:04,440 --> 00:13:06,400
These white bones all have knife marks

217
00:13:10,160 --> 00:13:11,440
They must be from fifteen years ago

218
00:13:11,920 --> 00:13:12,800
The wronged souls of Wanling Township

219
00:13:20,720 --> 00:13:21,160
Sun An

220
00:13:22,480 --> 00:13:24,080
Open your eyes and look at these people who died in vain

221
00:13:25,480 --> 00:13:27,520
You ignored the shocking bloodbath of Wanling Township

222
00:13:27,680 --> 00:13:28,360
What is your crime?

223
00:13:29,080 --> 00:13:29,920
You shielded the murderers

224
00:13:29,920 --> 00:13:31,320
Hiding them beneath this bright and prosperous era

225
00:13:31,320 --> 00:13:31,960
What is your crime?

226
00:13:32,880 --> 00:13:34,440
You indulged murderers to rob merchants

227
00:13:34,440 --> 00:13:35,800
And accepted bribes. What is your crime?

228
00:13:37,560 --> 00:13:38,920
How are you fit to be an official of my Great Tang?

229
00:13:39,560 --> 00:13:40,760
How are you fit to be a person of my Great Tang?

230
00:13:41,640 --> 00:13:41,920
Guiyi

231
00:13:43,400 --> 00:13:44,000
Search the Sun residence thoroughly

232
00:13:44,960 --> 00:13:46,320
Escort Sun An to Chang'an immediately

233
00:13:46,840 --> 00:13:47,600
For conviction and execution

234
00:13:48,160 --> 00:13:48,360
Yes

235
00:13:51,200 --> 00:13:51,400
Let's go

236
00:13:58,520 --> 00:13:59,280
Greed...

237
00:14:00,600 --> 00:14:01,360
Greed, in the end

238
00:14:02,920 --> 00:14:03,920
What can one gain?

239
00:14:04,800 --> 00:14:05,360
What about Sun Jia?

240
00:14:06,440 --> 00:14:07,800
How do you plan to sentence him?

241
00:14:10,600 --> 00:14:11,200
Sun Jia

242
00:14:12,160 --> 00:14:12,920
Who is Sun Jia?

243
00:14:14,320 --> 00:14:17,160
On that Wanling Township register from fifteen years ago

244
00:14:18,640 --> 00:14:19,320
There is no such person

245
00:14:23,200 --> 00:14:23,480
Hey

246
00:14:25,600 --> 00:14:26,280
Hey, Lao Yao

247
00:14:26,640 --> 00:14:27,000
Hmm

248
00:14:27,360 --> 00:14:28,160
I have a favor to ask

249
00:14:28,920 --> 00:14:30,400
Oh, so polite

250
00:14:30,960 --> 00:14:31,440
Let's hear it

251
00:14:32,480 --> 00:14:34,760
Um, about me bumping into a ghost in Wanling Township

252
00:14:34,760 --> 00:14:36,160
Don't tell anyone when you get back to Chang'an

253
00:14:37,240 --> 00:14:38,200
That's hard to say

254
00:14:39,400 --> 00:14:39,920
Depends on my mood

255
00:14:40,680 --> 00:14:42,680
Depends on your mood? You say it depends on your mood?

256
00:14:43,080 --> 00:14:44,040
Say "depends on my mood" again
